summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 20552 entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Lakewood Avenue from the south line of Lot Three (3) of Block Sixty-three (63) and Lot Twenty-two (22) of Block Sixty-nine (69) of Mt. Baker Park Addition to the City of Seattle, to the north line of Lot "A" of Block Sixty-four (64) and Lot "A" of Block Sixty-eight (68) of Mt. Baker Park Addition to the City of Seattle; all in the City of Seattle by grading and curbing the same and constructing concrete walks, all in accordance with Resolution No. 1951 of the City Council of the City of Seattle; and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Immediate Payment," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle, approved April 2nd, 1909.
